attributes.Long form description: The student changes the Joy-Cons to a comfort grip, changes to Joy-Con mode, and changes back to handheld mode. The student sets the Nintendo Switch into its kickstand mode and changes a game card. The student exchanges their Nintendo Switch's SD card and turns on the Nintendo Switch. The student turns off the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: Now please change the controller from handheld mode to the Joy-Con comfort grip.

attributes.Action sentence: The student changes the Joy-Cons to a comfort grip.

attributes.Transcription: There should be a button at the back that you need to press.
And then push up the controller.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The joy-con strap is for the joy-con controller not for the display.

attributes.Transcription: You'll have to take the red and blue controller and put it onto the controller grip in the back right.
Slide it from the top to the bottom.
Nice. Well done.
Now please change the controller from the Joy-Con comfort grip to two Joy-Cons.

attributes.Action sentence: The student changes to Joy-Con mode.

attributes.Transcription: So take out the controllers again.
You will have to match the plus and the minus... at the front of the controller.
At the front, at the top there should be a plus of the blue controller or a minus that you need to match with the plus or minus of the black part.
It's currently the wrong way around
Make sure to also lock the white lock in place at the bottom.

attributes.Action sentence: The student changes to Joy-Con mode.

attributes.Transcription: You will just have to press it indoors.
At the top, there should be again a plus or minus.
So turn around the controller for a second, and flip it around again
The other way.
And lock in place the white part.
Nice. Well done.
Now please change the controller from the two Joy-Cons back into the handled mode.

attributes.Action sentence: The student changes the Joy-Cons back to handheld mode.

attributes.Transcription: You'll first have to disengage the lock.
You will have to attach the green and the blue and the red controllers.
Nice. Well done.
Now please stand the Nintendo on the table using the kickstand.

attributes.Action sentence: The student sets the Nintendo Switch into its kickstand mode.

attributes.Transcription: You just have to pull it out.
Nice. Well done.
Now please change the game card of the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student changes a game card.

attributes.Transcription: The game card is on the top right of the Nintendo Switch.
Nicely done.
Now please change the micro SD card in the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges their Nintendo Switch's SD card.

attributes.Transcription: The micro sd card is under the kickstand
It should be at the bottom of the kickstand.
Nice. Well done.
Now please turn on the Nintendo switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns on the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: Nice. Well done.
Now please turn off the Nintendo switch again.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns off the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: Go to the power options and then power off.
Nicely done
You can stop the recording now.
